CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 1, 1952, pg. 22, reads: "Courier Analyst Returns Home - When the Eisenhower Special Train arrived at Pennsylvania Station Monday night, among those who alighted was Pittsburgh's own John L. Clark, Courier analyst, who as ah excellent batting average on election contests to date. Clark has picked Ike to win this time. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd, including Pittsburgh Courier newspaper analyst John L. Clark wearing light colored overcoat in center, police officers on right, and photographer on left, gathered in Pennsylvania Station for arrival of Eisenhower's train
